evaluations.proposal_1_title: Synthesis of Molecular Data for Cancer Cell Evolution

dimensions.justification: Both proposals aim to synthesize molecular data to understand disease, but they focus on entirely different biological domains: cancer evolution versus neurodegeneration.
The proposals target completely different disease contexts (cancer vs. neurodegeneration) and will therefore use distinct, non-overlapping patient datasets.
Both proposals employ a similar high-level computational data synthesis approach, but the specific analytical tools and models will differ due to the distinct biological questions and data types.
The proposals aim to contribute novel insights to two entirely separate fields of study, cancer biology and neurodegenerative disease research, respectively.
Both proposals request an identical budget ($500k) and timeline (3 years) and require similar computational resources, though the specific scientific expertise of the collaborators differs.
